 JOHANNESBURG - Stockists of school uniforms say prices have increased around 20%  since January last year, adding yet another cost to be picked up by parents. Inland schools are opening for the 2023 school year on Wednesday and many parents have been standing in long queues at school uniform suppliers to get what they need. Back to School | Gauteng parents frustrated Parents say that while costs are higher, they are left with little choice. eNCA’s reporter Pule Letshwiti-Jones has the details in the video above. #eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones reports. #DStv403